28/04/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Czech President Vaclav Klaus voiced his country's support for Montenegro's bids to join the EU and NATO during talks Wednesday (April 27th) with counterpart Filip Vujanovic in Cetinje.
He warned that the country should not hurry to join the bloc but should instead focus on reforms in order to become fully prepared for membership.
Vujanovic said that Montenegro will work to meet European standards.
(RTCG, Radio Free Europe - 27/04/11)
